.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.COMPARE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.compare \- Temporal.PlainDate.compare()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.PlainDate.compare()\f[B]\f[R] static method
returns a number (\-1, 0, or 1) indicating whether the first date comes
before, is the same as, or comes after the second date.
Equivalent to comparing the year, month, and day fields of the
underlying ISO 8601 dates.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
Temporal.PlainDate.compare(date1, date2)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]date1\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instance
representing the first date to compare.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]date2\f[R]
The second date to compare, converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R]
object using the same algorithm as \f[CR]date1\f[R].
.SS Return value
Returns \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if \f[CR]date1\f[R] comes before
\f[CR]date2\f[R], \f[CR]0\f[R] if they are the same, and \f[CR]1\f[R] if
\f[CR]date1\f[R] comes after \f[CR]date2\f[R].
They are compared by their underlying date values, ignoring their
calendars.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using Temporal.PlainDate.compare()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-08\-02\(dq);
console.log(Temporal.PlainDate.compare(date1, date2)); \f[I]// \-1\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-31\(dq);
console.log(Temporal.PlainDate.compare(date1, date3)); \f[I]// 1\f[R]
.EE
.SS Comparing dates in different calendars
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 8, day: 1 });
\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({
  year: 2021,
  month: 8,
  day: 1,
  calendar: \(dqislamic\-umalqura\(dq,
});
\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({
  year: 2021,
  month: 8,
  day: 1,
  calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq,
});
console.log(date1.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-08\-01\(dq\f[R]
console.log(date2.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2582\-12\-17[u\-ca=islamic\-umalqura]\(dq\f[R]
console.log(date3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq\-001739\-04\-06[u\-ca=hebrew]\(dq\f[R]
console.log(Temporal.PlainDate.compare(date1, date2)); \f[I]// \-1\f[R]
console.log(Temporal.PlainDate.compare(date1, date3)); \f[I]// 1\f[R]
.EE
.SS Sorting an array of dates
The purpose of this \f[CR]compare()\f[R] function is to act as a
comparator to be passed to \f[CR]Array.prototype.sort()\f[R] and related
functions.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dates = [
  Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 8, day: 1 }),
  Temporal.PlainDate.from({
    year: 2021,
    month: 8,
    day: 1,
    calendar: \(dqislamic\-umalqura\(dq,
  }),
  Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 8, day: 1, calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq }),
];

dates.sort(Temporal.PlainDate.compare);
console.log(dates.map((d) \f[B]=>\f[R] d.toString()));
\f[I]// [ \(dq\-001739\-04\-06[u\-ca=hebrew]\(dq, \(dq2021\-08\-01\(dq, \(dq2582\-12\-17[u\-ca=islamic\-umalqura]\(dq ]\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
